4 (c) As used in this section, "merger and acquisition broker" has
5 the meaning set forth in 15 U.S.C. 78o(b)(13)(E)(iv), as in effect on
6 July 1, 2026.
7 (d) As used in this section, "passive buyer" means a person or
8 a group of people that acquire ownership of an eligible privately
9 held company, but does not direct the management or policies of
10 the eligible privately held company after the transaction.
11 (e) As used in this section, "shell company" has the meaning set
12 forth in 15 U.S.C. 78o(b)(13)(E)(v), as in effect on July 1, 2026.
13 (f) Except as provided in subsections (g) and (h), a merger and
14 acquisition broker shall be exempt from registration as a
15 broker-dealer under this article.
16 (g) A merger and acquisition broker is not exempt from
17 registration under subsection (f) if the merger and acquisition
18 broker does any of the following:
19 (1) Directly or indirectly, in connection with the transfer of
20 ownership of an eligible privately held company, receives,
21 holds, transmits, or has custody of the funds or securities to be
22 exchanged by the parties to the transaction.
23 (2) Engages on behalf of an issuer in a public offering of any
24 class of securities that is registered, or is required to be
25 registered, with the Securities and Exchange Commission
26 under 15 U.S.C. 78l.
27 (3) Engages on behalf of an issuer in a public offering of any
28 class of securities that the issuer files, or is required to file,
29 periodic information, documents, and reports under 15 U.S.C.
30 78o(d).
31 (4) Engages on behalf of any party in a transaction involving
32 a shell company other than a business combination related
33 shell company.
34 (5) Directly or indirectly, through any of its affiliates,
35 provides financing related to the transfer of ownership of an
36 eligible privately held company.
37 (6) Assists any party in obtaining financing from an
38 unaffiliated third party without:
39 (A) complying with all applicable laws in connection with
40 providing the assistance described in this subdivision,
41 including, if applicable, Regulation T (12 CFR 220 et seq.);
